Questions:
By changing the order of integration, write each expression as one iterated integral:
(1) integral from 0 to 1 dx integral from 0 to x f(x, y) dy + integral from 1 to 2 dx integral from 0 to 2-x f(x, y) dy;
(2) integral from 0 to 1/2 dy integral from y^2 to y f(x, y) dx + integral from 1/2 to 1 dy integral from y^2 to 1-y f(x, y) dx;
(3) integral from 1 to sqrt(3) dx integral from 1 to x^2 f(x, y) dy + integral from sqrt(3) to sqrt(8) dx integral from 1 to 8-x^2 f(x, y) dy.

Answers:
(1) integral from 0 to 1 dy integral from y to 2-y f(x, y) dx;
(2) integral from 0 to 1 dx integral from x to sqrt(x) f(x, y) dy;
(3) integral from 1 to 3 dy integral from sqrt(y) to sqrt(8-y) f(x, y) dx.

Fig. 62: integral from 0 to 2 dy integral from y/2 to (y+4)/3 f(x, y) dx + integral from 2 to 4 dy integral from y/2 to (16-y)/3 f(x, y) dx;
Fig. 63: integral from 1 to 3 dx integral from 1 to (x+2)/2 f(x, y) dy + integral from 3 to 4 dx integral from (3x-5)/2 to (x+2)/2 f(x, y) dy;
Fig. 64: integral from -1 to 0 dx integral from 1-sqrt(1-x^2) to 1 f(x, y) dy + integral from 0 to 1 dx integral from 1-x to 1 f(x, y) dy;
Fig. 65: integral from 0 to 1 dx integral from sqrt(1-(x-1)^2) to 3x f(x, y) dy + integral from 1 to 3 dx integral from sqrt(4-(x-2)^2) to 3x f(x, y) dy + integral from 3 to 4 dx integral from sqrt(4-(x-2)^2) to 4 f(x, y) dy.

